{{doc/start}}
Navigation box listing all buildings in Foundry, grouped by function. Placed at the bottom of every building page. Built on [[Template:Navbox2]].

== Usage ==
<pre>{{Navbox Buildings}}</pre>

No parameters. Place at the very end of a building article, after all sections.

== Groups ==
The navbox is divided into the following categories:

{| class="wikitable"
! Group !! Contents
|-
| Production || Crafting and processing buildings (smelters, assemblers, chemical processors, etc.)
|-
| Modular Buildings || Buildings with a base + detachable module structure (Fracking Tower, Air Intake, etc.)
|-
| Assembly Lines || The full set of Assembly Line components
|-
| Power Generation || Buildings that produce electricity (generators, turbines, solar panels, etc.)
|-
| Power Distribution || Batteries, power poles, and transformers
|-
| Solid Item Logistics || Conveyors, loaders, freight elevators, cargo shuttles, shipping pads
|-
| Liquid Handling || Pipes, pipelines, pumps, tanks, and pumpjacks
|-
| Resource Gathering || Mining drones, geological scanners, and extractors
|-
| Storage || Containers and logistic containers
|-
| Rail Transport || Train stations, loading stations, and signals
|-
| Construction || Construction and transport ship ports and warehouses
|-
| Data System || Data cables, processors, memory cells, evaluators, and sources
|-
| Science || Research Servers
|-
| Infrastructure || Lights, doors, stairs, elevators, walkways, signs, and other structural pieces
|-
| Recycling || Resource Separator and Scrap Recycler
|-
| Miscellaneous || Decorative items, special buildings, and development placeholders
|}

== Maintenance ==
This navbox is maintained by hand. When a new building is added to the game:
# Add the page link under the appropriate group in <code>[[Template:Navbox Buildings]]</code>.

Building pages themselves are generated automatically and already include <code><nowiki>{{Navbox Buildings}}</nowiki></code> at the bottom.

== Notes ==
* Module buildings (e.g. Air Intake Module) are listed separately under Modular Buildings rather than alongside their base.
{{doc/end}}
